"{\"uid\": \"mbr.co.uk-news-tom-pidcock-suffers-front-puncture-in-olympic-mountain-bike-xco-race-while-in-the-lead-440293\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Pidcock, the defending Olympic champion, punctures on lap 4 and loses 36 seconds in fumbled wheel change.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 105, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Drama struck for the defending champion and Olympic favourite, Tom Pidcock, on lap four of the men's Olympic XCO race at \\u00c9lancourt Hill near Paris, when he suffered a front puncture while in the lead.\", \"from\": 107, \"to\": 307, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 170, \"end\": 181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Pidcock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\"}, {\"begin\": 248, \"end\": 253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999883877991, \"rank\": 1.1612223769642545e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although Pidcock, who'd broken away from the chasing pack with French star Viktor Koretzky, flatted close to the technical zone - where riders can get mechanical assistance - his mechanics were not ready with a spare front wheel, compounding the time lost on track.\", \"from\": 308, \"to\": 573, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 371, \"end\": 377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.6909564748137259, \"rank\": 0.32220518209387095, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Around ten seconds was lost in the hunt for a new wheel, and a further 24 seconds in the pit stop, leaving Pidcock over half a minute behind Koretzky once he'd got going again.\", \"from\": 574, \"to\": 750, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sensibly Pidcock elected to walk down a drop-off just after the puncture occurred, but again, this also added to the gap Koretzky was able to pull out.\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 902, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ELANCOURT, FRANCE - JULY 29: (L-R) Mathias Flueckiger of Team Switzerland and Thomas Pidcock of Team Great Britain compete during the Men's Cross-Country on day three of the Olympic Games Paris 2024 at Elancourt Hill on July 29, 2024 in Elancourt, France.\", \"from\": 904, \"to\": 1159, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 904, \"end\": 913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\", \"score\": 0.9725613440037943, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"ELANCOURT\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\"}, {\"begin\": 961, \"end\": 977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A1_Team_Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9999993457170016, \"rank\": 6.542833924482225e-07, \"text\": \"Team Switzerland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A1_Team_Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A1_Team_Switzerland\"}, {\"begin\": 982, \"end\": 996, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Pidcock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\"}, {\"begin\": 1000, \"end\": 1018, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A1_Team_Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999999435290208, \"rank\": 5.64710403652571e-08, \"text\": \"Team Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A1_Team_Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A1_Team_Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 1141, \"end\": 1150, \"title\": \"http://dbpe